<br>
Conversely, the Circle of Sisters is not in the habit of dictating to its members what they should and should not do. If there are individual Sisters that choose to associate with the Sisters of Myth (or any other group), that is their choice. It does not mean that our guild approves of these associations, only that we give our members the freedom to make their own decisions about who they do or do not want to have as their friends.<br>
<br>
Note that this does NOT mean that the Sisters absolve our members of all responsibility for their actions. Regardless of whom a Sister chooses to associate with, we still expect that Sister to uphold the principles of our guild: respect for others and striving for peace in a chaotic world.<br>
<br>
[See this link for the principles of the Circle of Sisters: www.cosfv.com/rules.html]<br>
<br>
In summary, if an individual Sister chooses to associate with those that espouse &quot;evil&quot; ideals, for whatever reasons (RP, simple friendship, whatever) they may do so, provided that she continues to adhere to our own code of conduct. But this does not mean that our guild does, or ever will, approve of the path of evil and those that follow it.<br>
<br>
If anyone has any questions about any of this, please email me at: eq_nysa@yahoo.com.<br>
<br>
